CBRE is pleased to offer 9 Colindia Avenue, Neutral Bay to the market.

The property presents an unrivaled opportunity to acquire an exclusively positioned apartment block investment located in Sydney's esteemed Lower North Shore.

9 Colindia Avenue, Neutral Bay is being offered for sale via Auction on Tuesday, 7 March 2017 at 10.30am (AEDT).

The property benefits from the following attributes:

- 8 well-presented 1 bedroom apartments
- Rental Income: $224,796*
- 531sqm* site area zoned R4
- On-site parking for 3 cars
- Premier city and harbour views
- Chance to develop a high-end, boutique residential conversion
- Situated 200m* from Clark Road Village shops
- Potential to strata (STCA)

*Approximate

For more information, please contact the selling agents.

CBRE as the exclusive sales agents are pleased to present, Shop 7, 81-91 Military Road, Neutral Bay.

The property is a self-contained shop with 1 basement parking space. The property is situated on a prominent corner with exposure to two high trafficked streets opposite the Oaks Hotel and surrounded by restaurants, cafes and leading retailers including Woolworths and Coles.

The property benefits from the following key
attributes:

• Large glass shop front and signage to prominent corner with double street exposure
• Excellent exposure to both foot and vehicular traffic at busy intersection
• Monthly tenant appealing to owner occupiers or investors
• Self-contained 36sqm* shop with 1 basement car space 


The property will be sold via public auction on Tuesday, 15th September 2020 at AuctionWORKS (Live stream and online bidding available)

*approximate

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
- Leased to National Australia Bank (NAB)
- Estimated fully lease
- Land area 316.2sqmd income $290,000 pa*
- Zoned B4 (Mixed use)
- Rear lane access (Military Lane)

CBRE, as the exclusive listing agent, is pleased to present 244 Military Road, Neutral Bay. 

Located 3.5km* north of the Sydney CBD and in the centre of Sydney’s robust Lower North Shore region, this two-storey freehold retail property rests on 106sqm* of B4 - Mixed Use zoned land. The property has significant frontage and signage to Military Road which connects Neutral Bay to the city, M1 Motorway and north towards the Northern Beaches. Neutral Bay is listed as Sydney's 10th Most Liveable Suburb on the Urban Living Index.

The underlying B4 Mixed Use zoning and 16m height limit positions the property for redevelopment (STCA). The property also sits within Stage 1 of the Military Road Planning Corridor Study which proposes an increase in density to support jobs and housing in the rapidly growing suburb.

244 Military Road benefits from the following key attributes: 

•	Total NLA of 156sqm*
•	5.1m* frontage and significant signage opportunities (STCA ) to Military Road
•	High exposure location with 50,000* cars passing daily  
•	Fully integrated security system
•	Split system air-conditioning on each floor 
•	Kitchenette & bathroom on each floor plus shower
•	Top floor Rear & front balcony
•	Built in 2000 with depreciation benefits
•	B4 Mixed Use Zoning with 16m height limit providing significant development potential (STCA)
•	Situated within Stage 1 of the Military Road Planning Corridor Study which proposes an increase in density to support jobs and housing in the rapidly growing suburb.
•	Offered with vacant possession suitable for occupiers, investors or developers


244 Military Road, Neutral Bay will be sold via Private Treaty. 

For more information or to request access to the due diligence room, please contact the exclusive selling agents. 

 *Approx.
